`Landez` builds MBTiles files from a Mapnik stylesheet, given a list of bounding boxes and zoom levels.

It uses `mbutil` from Mapbox https://github.com/mapbox/mbutil


=====
USAGE
=====

::

    from landez import MBTilesBuilder
    
    mb = MBTilesBuilder(stylefile="yourstyle.xml", filepath="dest.mbtiles")
    mb.add_coverage(bbox=(-90.0, -180.0, 180.0, 90.0), 
                    zoomlevels=[0, 1])
    mb.run()


